President Obama announced his intent to nominate four individuals to key administration posts: Frank Kendall III for Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition and Technology, Daniel Werfel for Controller at the Office of Federal Financial Management, Susan Tsui Grundmann for Chairman of the Merit Systems Protection Board, and Anne M. Wagner for Member of the Merit Systems Protection Board with the designation of Vice Chair. Frank Kendall III has over 35 years of experience in engineering, management, defense acquisition, and national security affairs. Daniel Werfel has been the Deputy Controller at the Office of Management and Budget since March 2006. Susan Tsui Grundmann has served as General Counsel to the National Federation of Federal Employees since 2002 and has successfully litigated cases in federal courts. Anne M. Wagner is currently the General Counsel of the Personnel Appeals Board of the U.S. Government Accountability Office and has experience in labor and employment law.